  "commentary": "With SPX at 6604.53 sitting just above the massive +71.2B gamma wall at 6600, dealers are actively selling into this strength as they hedge their long gamma positions. The PIN regime with 336.9B total GEX creates a strong gravitational pull toward the 6600 strike, while the GEX flip at 6589 provides downside support - any dip below 6589 would flip dealers short gamma and accelerate selling. Watch for continued resistance at the 6600-6610 corridor where dealers have over 118B in positive gamma to hedge, while the 6500 level (-4.5B negative gamma) remains the key breakdown point that would trigger dealer buying.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned around 6600 with choppy action between 6590-6610.",
